column5: OH  Ok I,ll give it a go. Im go,er after all. LMAO
Lookin nice  http://www.theweathernetwork.com/index.php?product=fourteenday&placecode=caon0663
Sure is Lew. Was hoping to get away Thurs........but Friday it will have to be. Meeting Brian (Misfish) in Barrie and then headed up, Expect to be enjoying a cold one on the dock mid to late AM.
Weather looks good Lew !!  Hopefully we should be there late AM on Friday as well.  I got a couple of things for the prize table that u will like if you are either a muskie fisherman or a golfer
Need to know if there are Propane BBQ,s there? Would like to add to the dinner Saturday.
Just noticing on the calender that the G2G falls two and three days after the full moon.
Btian they have Weber grills that use Charcoal.   Art

Yer on the shine arent ya?  Ok ,i,ll try my best with that. Not sure how it,s going to work out doing indirect heat,but something tells me with the smoke and coals,it may turn out better then home. Im going to need two of them for about 4 hours.
And it falls on FATHERSDAY. Lucky you.
That's how I got my permission slip signed Brian
Looks like I can make the 25 minute drive to Lakair this year and maybe even spend the night(In my truck)...I'm 80% sure ... really lookin' forward to it!  Randy

So i just got back frome fishing on the west arm did not do to well cough some pickerel lots of rock bass and perch. But the water was still at 65.6 for the most part i really hope that the water warm's up to get the big guy's moving around  And Randy hope you make it would be great to meet another northerner
So that weekend,the real fishing season is open right?
Yup - Saturday is opening day to go after the big girls.  I hope they're hungry. I believe Bass come in the following Saturday - the 25th  (If memory serves me right)
You are correct. I thought it was a different date up there. Oh well,guess I,ll just bring the heavy gear.LOL
I'd like to add some Scalloped Potatoes to the dinner if no one objects...will need an oven though...  Maureen
Hey Randy.. I just might be in MY TRUCK too.. lol
Diane and I are in cabin 5 this year Mo but I don't know if it has an oven or not, but if it does your more than welcome to use it.
Thanks Lew, between you and another offer I should be good to go, who knows maybe I'll make an Au Gratin too  See you there and looking forward to meeting Diane  Maureen
I think all the cabins have ovens so you should be good to go Mo!!  Sure hope you can make it Randy and Shelley.  Brian, I'm sure Les & Kev won't mind if you use their propane BBQ for a bit

Who wants to do a shore lunch on Tombstone Friday afternoon For those of you who have never had the pleasure Tombstone is an island at the mouth of West Bay leading into the Muskrats. It overlooks the West Bay and all its glory. One of the best elevated stone islands with a view and a great place to park your boat and have shore lunch. Last year we missed the opportunity to do the event due to planning issues but this year I would like to put the wheels in motion and get everyone out there for a fun afternoon.  ChrisK
How are you going to get there Chris.....
Maybe he could water ski behind the plane.....  The bridge is gonna suck though... I'm not going under it !
I'm sure you could do it Wayne, just keep the rods in the plane.....
Are you sure you will have enough eyes to feed all by then?   Been awhile Chris,but I can still handle a TILLER.   That would be extream and would pay to see.
It's a 75 tiller Brian, you up to it?
As long as the two Chris's don't play outboard motor and tiller in the cabin things will be o.k.   Art
Hell, I can handle a 1975 tiller with a blind fold, no prob.
Funny boy....LOL  I should have said 75 horse tiller.
Time to wind up and get planning for the fun this year.  After all the trophy is leaving Canada this year for it's new home in the USA.   Art

That's right.  Already have a nice spot picked out on the entertainment center for it.   really looking forward to catching up with good friends I only see once a year.   Looks like we'll have some new faces this year and make some new friends.  Just an all around dang good/fun time.     Oh yeah - that 50 incher out there ... I got my camera ready for ya.  We're bringing our son-in-law this time.   This will be his first ever Canadian Adventure and he's been looking forward to this since late last year.   Oh yeah - no dogs on this trip.
But what if Leah and I drop in from the sky, fish off the dock and fly away with said trophy at the end of the day.....
ha ha. think i might go and stock up that little bay not to far away with all the big ones that i catch then i will win the trophy
Too bad you are not bringing the girls this year Rich.

WHAT?!?!?!? Nobody will recognize ya's! LOL   I had really hoped to make the trip this year but may not be able to. If I do, I'll boatless and homeless while I'm up there! My boat is still in storage and I haven't made any reservations because this past month has been crazy to say the least! It may not stop me from shooting up there for the weekend but I won't know until last minute.
If you can show up Brian, do so I'll make sure you're looked after with roof and boat. Mind ya ChrisK is in charge of my boat keys so you'll likely have to spend time with him.....
Hey Brian, if I manage to make it for the day I'd be happy to split the cost of a boat rental on Saturday...  maureen

I appreciate the offer Chris. I can think of worse things than being stuck in a boat with ChrisK; (A)it's not enclosed and (B)at least we'll find fish!   Cool Mo, might just take you up on it but don't wait to make plans; I may not make it there at all.
Come and get it !! :tease:  :tease:
I don't know Chris... it's a pretty foamy looking beer, have you got a fresh one?
What you talkin bout Wayne ?? That was a fresh one with some mighty fine head on it. You must be drinkin that watered down store bought brew that doesn't hold a head on it for more than 10 seconds
The tourneys on Saturday?
Yes Sir.

And the fish fry, the picnic, the camp fires, and all the fire-side chats and sharing of stories.  (Some true and maybe some stretched a bit).  Looking forward to putting some faces to some new names.  Oh yeah, and some items to sweeten the prize table.  Picked up some stuff at the Harrisburg Sport show this year.  Hope I remember to pack it.

It is amazing how the prize table fills up from all of the generous donations from those that show up. We also like to thank our sponsors that have been very generous also even when they can not make it to the get together. It seems every year everyone gets a little something for their enjoyment no matter what place they come in. So if you have something for the table new or used feel free to bring it with you it will find a new home and you can be sure a smile from it's new owner. Don't forget to bring your appetite T.J. and the crew cook up a mean mess of fish.    Art
I,ll be bring a box of plastic baits and hooks for the table.

Just two weeks from right now .... I'll be within two hours of Lakair. Looking forward to seeing old friends and making some new ones. Anxiety is building to get out on the water for the first time this year.
I'm looking forward to seeing you and Patsy again Rich but Brook is upset that your not bringing her friends.
When are you guys headed up Chris? Barbara and I should arrive late morning Friday.
Uncertain yet John.
Diane and I will be arriving early Thursday afternoon Rich and it'll be good to see you and Patsy again.
Ditto.  Maybe we can check out the F150's.
I,ll be leaving mine at home.Take the focus. Easier on the wallet.   Just in time to open the bar.
Just in time to open the bar.   Sounds perfect Brian...
